    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1624"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1624">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of the Navy</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 13, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The following recommendation of the Joint Board,
                    dated November 27, 1911, has been approved by the President, under date of
                    December 12: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>2. That an understanding be reached with Panama to prevent the
                            establishments of private and commercial wireless installations in its
                            territory.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Accordingly, I have the honor to request that necessary steps be taken by the
                    State Department to accomplish the desired understanding with the Republic of
                    Panama in definite terms, so as to prevent the establishments of private and
                    commercial wireless installations in its territory.</p>
                <p>I have the honor, further, to request that negotiations to this end be commenced
                    as soon as practicable, as it has come to the attention of the Navy Department
                    that the establishment of a wireless system in Panama is being contemplated,
                    which would seriously interfere with our national policy regarding means of
                    communication in the vicinity of the Canal Zone, as set forth in the
                    above-quoted recommendation.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beekman Winthrop.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
